  "prompt": "Where does the word \"suicide\" come from?",
  "response": "The word \"suicide\" comes from the Latin roots \"sui,\" meaning \"of oneself,\" and \"caedere,\" meaning \"to kill.\" Therefore, it literally translates to \"to kill oneself.\" The term has been used in English since the late 16th century and reflects the act of intentionally causing one's own death. The usage and understanding of the term have evolved over time, but its etymological roots emphasize the personal aspect of the act.",
